{"cursor":"12749","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = The Right Honourable |name = The Lord\nHoffmann |native_name = |native_name_lang = |honorific-suffix = PC |image =\n|imagesize = |smallimage = \n|alt = |caption = |order = |office = Second Senior Lord of Appeal in Ordinary\n|term_start = 2007 |term_end = 20 April 2009 |monarch = Elizabeth II\n|predecessor = The Lord Nicholls of Birkenhead |successor = The Lord Hope of\nCraighead |constituency = |majority = |order2 =  |office2 = Lord of Appeal in Ordinary\n|term_start2 = 1995 |term_end2 = 2009 |alongside2 =  |vicepresident2 =  |viceprimeminister2 =  |deputy2 =  |lieutenant2 =  |monarch2 =  |president2 =  |primeminister2 =  |governor2 =  |succeeding2 =  |predecessor2 =  |successor2 = The Lord\nCollins of Mapesbury |constituency2 =  |majority2 =  |birth_name = Leonard Hubert Hoffmann |birth_date =\n|birth_place = Cape Town, South Africa |spouse = Gillian Hoffmann ; 2 children |death_date = |death_place = |alma_mater =\nUniversity of Cape Town The Queen's College, Oxford |occupation = Jurist}}\n\n'Leonard Hoffmann, Baron Hoffmann', PC (born 8 May 1934), is a retired senior\nBritish judge. He served as a Lord of Appeal in Ordinary from 1995 to 2009. Well\nknown for his lively decisions and willingness to break with convention, he has\nhad an especially large impact on shareholder actions in UK company law, in\nrestricting tort liability for public authorities, human rights and on\nintellectual property law, in particular patents. He is also a Non-permanent\nJudge of the Court of Final Appeal of Hong Kong.\n","linknr":195,"url":"Leonard_Hoffmann,_Baron_Hoffmann","recorded":1375075982,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Leonard_Hoffmann,_Baron_Hoffmann&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Leonard_Hoffmann,_Baron_Hoffmann&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/lic